abstract: National Assn of Realtors reports sales of used homes in May were up 5.1 percent, leading to seasonally adjusted annual rate of 5.35 million.
lead_paragraph: The National Association of Realtors said the May sales rate put home-buying on pace for its best year since 2007.

headline.main: Home Sales Rose in May, Helped by Strong Hiring and Low Rates
headline.print_headline: Home Sales Rose in May, With Help From Strong Hiring and Low Rates
